<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 09 at 4:01AM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...HEAT INDEX VALUES BETWEEN 106 AND 110 DEGREES ARE EXPECTED
THIS AFTERNOON...
The combination of very warm temperatures and high dewpoints will
produce heat indices between 106 and 110 degrees across portions
of the lower and middle Rio Grande Valley as well as across inland
portions of Willacy and Kenedy counties this afternoon.
Residents with outdoor activities planned are urged to drink
plenty of water, wear light weight and light colored clothing and
take frequent breaks from the heat. Young children and pets should
never be left unattended in vehicles under any circumstances.
This is especially true during warm or hot weather when car
interiors can reach lethal temperatures in a matter of minutes.</description>
